description:
Create the `useAgentStream(owner, repo, sessionId)` hook that connects to the agent session SSE stream endpoint and provides incremental token delivery for real-time response rendering.

The hook connects to `GET /api/repos/:owner/:repo/agent/sessions/:id/stream` via the SSE infrastructure (ticket-based auth). It processes three event types:
- `token` events: `{ type: 'token', data: { content: '...' } }` — appends content to the accumulating response
- `done` events: `{ type: 'done', data: {} }` — marks stream complete
- `error` events: `{ type: 'error', data: { message: '...' } }` — marks stream errored

Returned interface:
```typescript
interface AgentStreamState {
  streaming: boolean;
  currentTokens: string;
  connected: boolean;
  reconnecting: boolean;
  error: Error | null;
  subscribe: (sessionId: string) => void;
  unsubscribe: () => void;
}
```

The hook integrates with the existing `SSEProvider` context. It uses `useSSEChannel('agent_session_{sessionId}')` internally. On disconnect, it triggers exponential backoff reconnection (1s, 2s, 4s, 8s, max 30s). On reconnect, it replays missed tokens by re-fetching messages via the REST API and computing the diff.

Event deduplication: maintains a position counter to avoid duplicate tokens on reconnection replay.

Implementation target: `packages/ui-core/src/hooks/agents/useAgentStream.ts` (shared hook) and `apps/tui/src/hooks/useAgentStream.ts` (TUI adapter if needed for timeline integration).
